            "answer_text": "When Queen performed at Live Aid, there were 72,000 in the audience at Wembley, and about 100,000 in the audience in Philadelphia. However, Live Aid was broadcast globally, so additionally, approximately 1.9 billion people\u2014after Queen finished Radio GaGa\u2014saw or heard Freddie\u2019s \u201cay-oh\u201d vocal improv call-back sequence, especially the phenomenal long note at the 24 sec. point:  I\u2019m going to repeat myself: Almost 2 billion people heard this. Consequently, it is referred to as \u201cthe note heard around the world\u201d. ",
